<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="136" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,334,682,708]" box="[189,334,682,708]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,682,708]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,682,708]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,729,1388]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">
Erect herbs 
<quantity box="[332,451,729,756]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="cm" value="30.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="20.0">20–40 cm</quantity>
tall; roots rigid; single to multiple stems arising from the base, branching from the base to the apex, cylindrical, green, without yellowish glands, densely puberulous, trichomes short-clavate. Leaves all alternate, subsessile, chartaceous, laminas (0.6–)0.8–1 × 
<quantity box="[1162,1313,799,826]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="cm" value="0.09" valueMax="0.1" valueMin="0.08">0.08–0.1 cm</quantity>
, linear, apex acute, margins revolute, base acute, densely covered by small glandular trichomes on both sides. Racemes congested to shortly elongated 1.2–1.9 × 
<quantity box="[809,925,870,896]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="cm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1 cm</quantity>
, up to 
<quantity box="[1013,1096,870,896]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="cm" value="3.3">3.3 cm</quantity>
long after capsules have fallen; bracts 1.2 × 
<quantity box="[429,526,905,932]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate, apex acute, not ciliate, without yellowish glands, deciduous before anthesis, ca 2 times as long as the bracteoles; bracteoles elliptic, not ciliate; pedicel 
<quantity box="[1243,1333,940,967]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous. Flowers yellow, cream or whitish, 
<quantity box="[708,849,975,1002]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.45" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="5.45" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="5.4">5.4–5.5 mm</quantity>
long (without pedicel); outer sepals not ciliate, with yellow glands; lower outer sepals 1.5 × 
<quantity box="[722,816,1010,1037]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
, elliptic to ovate, apex obtuse; upper outer sepals 1.4–1.5 × 
<quantity box="[315,462,1046,1072]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.499999999999999" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="0.6499999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.7 mm</quantity>
, elliptic, apex rounded or slightly retuse; inner sepals (wings) 4.5 × 
<quantity box="[1298,1394,1046,1072]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
, elliptic, apex acute, margins not ciliate, longer than the mature fruits, without yellow glands; lateral petals 4.1 × 
<quantity box="[340,413,1116,1143]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
; keel ca 
<quantity box="[522,615,1116,1143]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
long, cristate, with yellow glands around the dorsal central vein, deciduous on mature fruits; crest 4–6-lobed; central lobes often bi-lobed to apex, style 
<quantity box="[1237,1330,1151,1178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long, erect, terminated by an oblique cymbiform pre-stigmatic cavity, posterior extremity with a conspicuously crested appendage with abundant trichomes and an anterior globose stigma. Capsules 3.5 × 
<quantity box="[1299,1395,1222,1248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
, subovate, bearing a double line of orange glands close to the central nervure, style deciduous in fruit; seeds ca 2.5 × 
<quantity box="[358,479,1292,1319]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="1.05" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="1.0">1–1.1 mm</quantity>
, obclavate, pubescent, trichomes 
<quantity box="[870,1010,1292,1319]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="0.15" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.2 mm</quantity>
long, without a ring of trichomes at the base of the seed, with two caruncular appendages 1.5 × 
<quantity box="[913,1054,1327,1354]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
reaching approximately ½ of the seed length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="136" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,645,1428,1454]" box="[189,645,1428,1454]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,645,1428,1454]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,645,1428,1454]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">Distribution, habitat, and phenology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1398,1474,1607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">
<taxonomicName authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,404,1474,1500]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bringelii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,404,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">Polygala bringelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[412,503,1475,1501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is endemic to the Jalapão region, 
<collectingRegion box="[905,1089,1474,1501]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">Tocantins State</collectingRegion>
, occurring in open natural grasslands with scattered shrubs (campo sujo and campo cerrado), occasionally near rocky outcrops, on sandy dry soils at altitudes of 350 to 550 meters in the municipalities of Mateiros and Ponte Alta do 
<collectingRegion box="[189,303,1580,1606]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,391,1580,1606]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,907,933]" captionTargetBox="[410,1177,266,831]" captionTargetId="figure-12@7.[410,1177,266,833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. Polygala bringelii J.F.B.Pastore &amp; Antar sp. nov. A. Habitat. B. Habit. C–D. Flowering branches. E. Inflorescence detail. Photos: G.M. Antar, in situ." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5211767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5211767/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Found fertile in January and from May to August.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="136" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,587,1645,1672]" box="[189,587,1645,1672]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,587,1645,1672]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,587,1645,1672]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">Preliminary conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1692,2001]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">
The estimated Area of Occupancy, with just 
<quantity box="[738,819,1692,1721]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="km" value="36.0">36 km</quantity>
², is low; the estimated Extent of Occurrence is 
<quantity box="[189,352,1727,1756]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.469542" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" unit="km" value="1469.542">1469.542 km</quantity>
². The species is currently known from ten collections, with most located inside the protected area of the Parque Estadual do Jalapão. Nominally protected, these areas are still subjected to uncontrolled anthropic fires, though recently diminished in number due to a new fire management program (Schmidt e 
<emphasis box="[420,456,1833,1859]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">t al</emphasis>
. 2018). Nearby areas, mostly in western 
<collectingRegion box="[925,1060,1833,1859]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">Bahia State</collectingRegion>
, have already been converted to agricultural use (
<bibRefCitation author="Borges L. M. &amp; Antar G. M." box="[418,678,1868,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" pagination="155 - 162" refId="ref6396" refString="Borges L. M. &amp; Antar G. M. 2016. Four they are! Broadening the description of Mimosa flabellifolia (Leguminosae Mimosoideae), a rare species from the Brazilian Cerrado. Phytotaxa 243: 155 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 243.2.5" type="journal article" year="2016">Borges &amp; Antar 2016</bibRefCitation>
), which is expanding towards the Jalapão with governmental incentives (
<bibRefCitation author="Antar G. M. &amp; Santos M. F. &amp; Sano P. T." box="[325,534,1903,1930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" pagination="55 - 71" refId="ref5842" refString="Antar G. M., Santos M. F. &amp; Sano P. T. 2018. Rediscovery and taxonomic reassessment of four angiosperms in the savannas of Jalapao, Central Brazil. Edinburgh Journal of Botany 75: 55 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0960428617000348" type="journal article" year="2018">
Antar 
<emphasis box="[403,456,1903,1929]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="136">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa-Silva R. G. &amp; Antar G. M." box="[548,894,1903,1930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="136" pagination="38 - 46" refId="ref6132" refString="Barbosa-Silva R. G. &amp; Antar G. M. 2020. Description vs deforestation: Couepia brevistaminea (Chrysobalanaceae), a new species on the frontier of agricultural expansion in the Brazilian savanna. Phytotaxa 471 (1): 38 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 471.1.4" type="journal article" year="2020">Barbosa-Silva &amp; Antar 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Although still regarded as data deficient, due to the precarious state of conservation of its suitable habitats, the species should be assessed as Endangered EN B1ab(i,ii,iii)+2ab(i,ii,iii) (IUCN 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="137" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,259,265,291]" box="[189,259,265,291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,259,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,259,265,291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,311,584]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[404,624,311,337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bringelii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[404,624,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Polygala bringelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[637,733,312,338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1261,311,337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosperma">
<emphasis box="[1071,1261,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P. trichosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with both species sharing the oblong-elliptic capsules with yellow glands along the mid-vein and linear leaves. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[310,440,381,407]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bringelii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[310,440,381,407]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P. bringelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[448,538,382,408]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[694,879,381,407]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichorperma">
<emphasis box="[694,879,381,407]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P. trichorperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the characters discussed in the diagnosis. Also, this new species is seemingly similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[749,1019,417,443]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[749,1019,417,443]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Polygala tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1028,1121,417,443]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(the other new species here described), both of them share similar sepals and yellowish flowers, differing mainly by the seed indument, with a ring of long trichomes at the seed base (vs seed without a ring of trichomes at the base in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[219,349,522,548]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bringelii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[219,349,522,548]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P. bringelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[357,449,523,549]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) and the keel crest in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[707,891,523,548]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[707,891,523,548]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P. tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[898,989,523,549]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is much more developed (ca twice the size) than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[383,513,557,583]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bringelii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[383,513,557,583]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P. bringelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[520,611,558,584]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
